\par \plain\f2\fs32\cf0\b\ul About ReMipDLX\plain\f2\fs32\cf3\b\ul 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs32\cf3\b\ul 
\par \plain\f2\fs20 \tab ReMipDLX was written by Neal White III to resample .mip and .wad files for Quake 1. Since the texture data itself is the same in Q2, ReMipDLX was written into Wally to give maximum sub-mip quality - in most cases, textures resampled by ReMipDLX will turn out with better quality than id's textures; try ReMipping one of the textures from Q2 to see what we mean. If you prefer the look of id's textures, you can set ReMipDLX to create sub-mips of similar quality. If you don't, feel free to go through all the Q2 textures and ReMip them all. Just bear in mind that there are over 2,000 of them :)
\par 
\par \tab \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\strike Using ReMipDLX\plain\f2\fs20\cf2 {\v Scribble26}\plain\f2\fs20 
